\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-720\f8\lang2057\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj 40.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls2\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-720\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang2057\loch\f8\fs24\lang2057 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs24\lang2057\i0\b0 While, as will be elaborated below, the Commission found that the impact on competition of the horizontal overlap in most of these markets is ameliorated by other factors \'96 for example the unusual dynamism of the FABs market or the merged entity\'92s relative
ly small market share in whisky \'96 the Commission\'92s narrow, category-based market definition was the basis for its finding of a substantial lessening of competition in the brandy, sparkling wine and gin markets and, accordingly, for its recommendation that 
the merged entity be compelled to divest itself of a number of brands in these markets.{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s19{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs60\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0 The Commission has only recommended remedies in two of these markets, viz. sparkling wine and brandy.  In the gin market, although it found that competition had been substantially lessened it declined to recommend a remedy on the grounds that litigation c
oncerning Distell\'92s distribution agreement with Gilbey\'92s (GUDV) was in process and its outcome would have a determinant effect on the merged entity\'92s market share. The matter is currently still subject to litigation, although agreement has been reached for
 the brand to remain with Distell until the matter has been decided by the courts. The Commission acknowledges however that \'91whoever ends up with control of the Gordon\'92s brand, will control the gin market\'92.}}}
{\*\cs60\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up10\rtlch\af11\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af11\langfe255\hich\f1\fs24\lang7177\loch\f1\fs24\lang7177  } }
