ose of brands with a cumulative market share of between 20-30% in volume.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang2057\loch\f8\fs24\lang2057 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-720\f8\lang2057\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj 42.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls2\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-720\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang2057\loch\f8\fs24\lang2057 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs24\lang2057\i0\b0 The merging parties on the other hand define the relevant market to include all alcoholic beverages, ranging from beer to spirits, including wine and FABs. The parties find that Distell\'92s post-merger market share in the national alcoholic beverage market, 
based on litres absolute alcohol, is 19.7%.{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s19{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs60\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0 When sorghum beer sales are taken into account, the market share drops to 17.2%. }}}
