\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s3\cf3\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs20\lang1025\ai\ab\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang1033\loch\f8\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-720\f8\lang2057\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj 49.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls2\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-720\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang2057\loch\f8\fs24\lang2057 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs24\lang2057\i0\b0 The Commission avers that competition authorities and courts elsewhere have, when confronted with the task of establishing a relevant market in the alcoholic beverages market, found for narrow, category-based markets.   The Commission particularly relies o
n US and European decisions in two prominent mergers, namely, the Guinness Plc and Grand Metropolitan Plc (1997) and Pernod Ricard/Diageo/Seagram Company Ltd (2001). These mergers were evaluated by the European Commission{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s19{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs60\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0 EC IV/M.938 and EC COMP/M.2268.}}}
{\*\cs60\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up10\rtlch\af11\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af11\langfe255\hich\f1\fs24\lang7177\loch\f1\fs24\lang7177  }and, in the case of Guinness/Gran
d Metropolitan, also by the US Federal Trade Commission. The Guinness/Grand Metropolitan merger was also investigated by the Australian ACCC. }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang2057\loch\f8\fs24\lang2057 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-720\f8\lang2057\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj 50.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls2\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-720\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang2057\loch\f8\fs24\lang2057 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs24\lang2057\i0\b0 In the Guinness / Grand Metropolitan transaction the European Commission based its market definition on spirit type.  This conclusion rested, {\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\i\loch\i inter alia}, on the finding that spirit drinkers display brand loyalty within the category of choice and also on th
e observation of well-entrenched \'91occasion-based\'92 consumption patterns which renders substitution on the basis of small price variations unlikely. The European Commission highlights the importance to competition in the spirits market of branding and its ap
plication to individual spirit types as a further justification for product markets not wider than that for each main spirit type, i.e. whisky (further segmented to differentiate Scotch whisky), brandy (further segmented to differentiate Cognac/Armagnac), 
rum, gin, vodka, tequila and flavoured spirits. }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang2057\loch\f8\fs24\lang2057 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-720\f8\lang2057\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj 51.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls2\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-720\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang2057\loch\f8\fs24\lang2057 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs24\lang2057\i0\b0 Note that the European Commission conceded the possibility of market segmentation based on price and quality differentiation observing that \'91a consumer who habitually drank a premium brand would not regard a cheaper one as providing an adequate substitute 
in terms of taste, image and so forth\'92.{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s19{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs60\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f4\fs20\lang1033\i0\b0 EC IV/M.938, para 18.}}}
{\*\cs60\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up10\rtlch\af11\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af11\langfe255\hich\f1\fs24\lang7177\loch\f1\fs24\lang7177 }  However, this observation did not, in the view of the European Commission, alter the finding that placed individual spirit categories at the centre of the relevant market definition but rather constituted the basis
 for a further segmentation, this time within the separate spirit categories.}
