anufacturers compete on image and branding, on the \'91extrinsics\'92 of the product, rather than on spirit category, the \'91intrinsics\'92. This means that, when faced with a significant price increase, a consumer that prefers a branded brandy is likely to switch to
 another branded spirit, possibly a white spirit or even a FAB, of equal \'91extrinsic\'92 appeal rather than to a less expensive, but less \'91extrinsically\'92 satisfying, product in the same traditional spirit category. }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang2057\loch\f8\fs24\lang2057 
